node.statement: Step 1.2.5 (q-12j leading correction): The leading non-vanishing non-melonic correction comes from the quantum 12j symbol of the second kind. Its large-j asymptotics scale as (log j)/j^{3/2}, giving an overall (log j)/j suppression of the non-melonic diagrams relative to the melonic ones, matching the classical scaling up to q-dependent prefactors.
